ping ingredients into mixing bowl and cook <b>10-12 min\/90°C\/\/speed <b> or until soft and tender. Place simmering basket over a bowl, and carefully drain liquid from cooked rhubarb through simmering basket. Reserve cooking liquid. Transfer rhubarb into a bowl and leave to cool to room temperature."},{"content":"Place rhubarb cooking liquid back into mixing bowl and cook <b>15-20 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid. Transfer syrup into a bowl and cool to room temperature."},{"content":"Carefully turn out panna cottas onto serving plates. Drizzle with cooled syrup and serve with reserved rhubarb."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Originating in Greece, mastic is an edible plant resin that can be used as a stabiliser. You can find mastic in specialty food stores, health food stores or online."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","25h 15m","6 portions"]}